On Mon, 20 Aug 2001 tlumley@u.washington.edu wrote:

>
> On Linux R1.3.0 (and current pre1.3.1 and pre1.4.0)
>  Sys.sleep(30)
> interrupt with CTRL-C
>  Sys.sleep(30)
> causes a segmentation fault. It doesn't happen under Windows (2000).
